results.name: For n>=1, let B_n(k) be the sequence defined by b(1)=1, b(2)=p_1, ..., b(n+2)=p_(n+1), thereafter (for k>=n+3) the smallest number not occurring earlier having at least one common factor with b(k-(n+1)), but none with b(k-1)*b(k-2)*...*b(k-n); a(n) is m such that B_n(m)=6.
comment: On the other hand, it seems likely that 6 never appears in A247665 (which has a different although related definition). - _N. J. A. Sloane_, Apr 26 2015
results.author: _Vladimir Shevelev_ and _Peter J. C. Moses_, Jan 22 2015
